<bug>
    <id>7101</id>
    <title>sysfs goes into readonly mode with host networking</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">When I run any docker image with host networking enabled, 'sysfs' enters readonly mode.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">"' bash
# before
$ cat /proc/mounts | grep sysfs
sysfs /sys sysfs rw,nosuid,nodev,noexec,relatime 0 0
$ docker run -it --rm --net=host ubuntu:12.04 echo "Hello World!"
Hello World!
# after
$ cat /proc/mounts | grep sysfs
sysfs /sys sysfs ro,nosuid,nodev,noexec,relatime 0 0
"'</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">I have to manually remount '/sys' to make it writable again 'mount -o remount,rw /sys'</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">"' bash
$ docker version 
Client version: 1.1.1
